3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Drift calculates TON/USDT funding rates hourly using a premium index derived from the perpetual-spot price differential. The vAMM (virtual Automated Market Maker) combined with DLOB (Decentralized Limit Order Book) ensures efficient price discovery through Just-in-Time liquidity auctions. Funding payments occur automatically every hour, with positions automatically adjusted in your margin account. The hybrid model allows for tighter spreads compared to pure AMM systems while maintaining the capital efficiency of vAMMs."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TON","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's status as a major Layer 1 blockchain with significant institutional backing creates substantial trading volume and funding rate volatility on Drift. The 1-hour funding frequency provides more granular arbitrage opportunities compared to 8-hour intervals on traditional CEXs. Drift's Solana-based infrastructure offers near-instant settlement, making it ideal for rapid funding rate arbitrage strategies with TON's often volatile funding environment."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"TON/USDT Historical Funding Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON funding rates on Drift have historically shown high volatility during ecosystem announcements and Telegram integration updates. The 1-hour intervals capture rapid sentiment shifts more effectively than 8-hour cycles, with rates frequently oscillating between -0.5% to +2% annually during major TON developments. Peak funding periods typically align with new dApp launches on the TON blockchain or Telegram feature rollouts. The shorter intervals on Drift often show less extreme rates compared to CEX counterparts due to more frequent rebalancing opportunities."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Drift's TON/USDT pair offers compelling arbitrage potential against Binance and OKX's 8-hour funding cycles. The vAMM+DLOB hybrid model provides better fill rates for larger positions while maintaining competitive spreads through JIT auctions. Arbitrageurs can capitalize on the 1-hour vs 8-hour funding differential, especially during periods of sustained directional bias in TON. Solana's sub-second finality enables rapid position adjustments, crucial for managing funding rate exposure across multiple venues."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Mitigation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Primary risks include Solana network congestion affecting position management and Drift's relatively lower liquidity compared to tier-1 CEXs during volatile periods. The hybrid liquidation mechanism, while sophisticated, can be complex during extreme market stress. Insurance fund protection exists but may be insufficient during major market dislocations. Arbitrageurs should monitor Drift's DLOB depth and vAMM utilization rates, as high utilization can lead to increased slippage and reduced arbitrage profitability."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Drift's 1-hour funding compare to CEX 8-hour cycles for TON?","answer":"Drift's hourly funding provides more granular arbitrage opportunities but typically results in lower absolute rates per interval. The shorter cycle reduces extreme rate accumulation but requires more active monitoring and position management compared to 8-hour CEX cycles."},{"question":"What makes TON/USDT funding rates particularly volatile on Drift?","answer":"TON's strong retail following and Telegram ecosystem developments create frequent sentiment shifts captured by Drift's hourly funding. The combination of institutional and retail flow, plus correlation with Telegram user growth metrics, drives funding rate volatility."},{"question":"How does Drift's vAMM+DLOB model affect TON funding calculations?","answer":"The hybrid model uses DLOB for price discovery while vAMM provides continuous liquidity, creating more stable premium calculations. JIT liquidity auctions help reduce artificial premium spikes that can skew funding rates on pure AMM systems."},{"question":"What are the main risks when arbitraging TON funding rates on Drift?","answer":"Key risks include Solana network dependency, lower liquidity during volatile periods, and complex liquidation mechanics. The DEX structure also means no traditional customer support for position management issues during network congestion."}]}]
